# Local context for Claude Code

> All teammates share this Linux server (and likely the same `root` account), so a single
> `CLAUDE.local.md` cannot disambiguate users. Convention: each teammate keeps their own
> file named `CLAUDE.local.<short-name>.md` (e.g. `CLAUDE.local.brightliao.md`). All such
> files are gitignored; only this `.example` is committed.
>
> At the start of each CC session, the user identifies themselves; CC then reads the
> matching `CLAUDE.local.<name>.md`. Update yours when your focus shifts — stale entries
> mislead other teammates' CC instances about ownership.

- **Name**: <e.g. 申昊 (shenhao)>
- **Role**: <lead | contributor | learning>
- **Where to find my current task / focus / hands-off scope**:
  - 单一真相源是仓库根的 [`docs/PHASE_PLAN.md`](docs/PHASE_PLAN.md)。
  - 文件开头的 **Current Phase** 段落里"团队成员与分工"和"Task 清单"两张表中我那一行就是当前授权范围。
  - 历史 phase 在文件后半部分，仅供回溯，不是当前授权范围。
  - 不要把 task 内容复制到这里 —— phase 切换时只改 PHASE_PLAN.md，避免两处不一致。
- **Notes for CC**: <preferences, expertise level, anything that should shape CC's defaults。
  比如 learning 角色应当请 CC 多解释"为什么"、不主动 git push / docker push、改动越界先 surface 等>
